In this Oval Office meeting, President Biden welcomes Prime Minister Draghi of Italy to the White House. They discuss their close alliance and cooperation in responding to the actions of Putin, particularly in relation to Ukraine. They express their condemnation of the invasion of Ukraine, support for sanctions against Russia, and commitment to helping Ukraine. Prime Minister Draghi emphasizes the need for peace and credible negotiations, as well as the importance of energy and food security. He also mentions that the situation in Ukraine will bring about a significant change in the European Union, and he appreciates President Biden's support for Europe and Italy. President Biden agrees on the importance of a strong European Union and the need for NATO and the EU to be in lockstep. They both express their delight at the meeting and their eagerness to continue the discussion.